fields.description: End-user's preferred postal address. The value of the address member is a JSON RFC8259 structure containing some or all of the members defined in the resource type
fields.name: Address

fields.description: End-user's preferred e-mail address. Its value MUST conform to the RFC 5322 addr-spec syntax.
fields.name: Email

fields.description: True if the end-user's e-mail address has been verified by the identity provider; otherwise, false. When this claim value is true, this means that your identity provider took affirmative steps to ensure that this e-mail address was controlled by the end-user at the time the verification was performed. If this claim value is false, or not mapped with any claim of the identity provider, the user is asked to verify email during sign-up if email is required in the user flow.
fields.name: Emailverified

fields.description: Surname(s) or family name of the end-user.
fields.name: Familyname

fields.description: Given name(s) or first name(s) of the end-user.
fields.name: Givenname

fields.description: End-user's full name in displayable form including all name parts, possibly including titles and suffixes, ordered according to the end-user's locale and preferences.
fields.name: Name

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: The claim provides the phone number for the user.
fields.name: Phonenumber

fields.description: True if the end-user's phone number has been verified; otherwise, false. When this claim value is true, this means that your identity provider took affirmative steps to verify the phone number.
fields.name: Phonenumberverified

fields.description: Subject - Identifier for the end-user at the Issuer.
fields.name: Sub
